# PHP Compatibility Rule

**Minimum Supported PHP Version: 7.4**

All production code in `plugin/`, `modules/`, and `providers/` MUST remain compatible with PHP 7.4.
Never use PHP 8-only syntax. Future PHP 8.x migration should require minimal changes.

## Forbidden Syntax

Never use:

- `match()`
- union types (`int|WP_REST_Response`, `string|int`, etc.)
- `mixed` type
- `never` type
- nullsafe operator (`?->`)
- constructor property promotion
- named arguments
- `readonly` properties
- `enum`
- attribute syntax (`#[]`)
- `str_contains()`, `str_starts_with()`, `str_ends_with()`

## PHP 7.4 Alternatives

```php
// ❌ match ($x) { 'a' => 1, default => 0 };
// ✅ switch ($x) { case 'a': return 1; default: return 0; }

// ❌ function foo(): int|WP_REST_Response
// ✅ function foo() { ... }  // @return int|WP_REST_Response in docblock if needed

// ❌ str_contains($haystack, $needle)
// ✅ strpos($haystack, $needle) !== false
```

## WordPress Coding Standards

- Follow [WordPress Coding Standards](https://developer.wordpress.org/coding-standards/wordpress-coding-standards/php/).
- Guard direct access: `if (!defined('ABSPATH')) exit;`
- Use WordPress APIs (`sanitize_*`, `wp_remote_*`, `register_rest_route`, etc.).
- Prefer `require_once` with `class_exists()` / `file_exists()` guards for cross-module loads.

## Activation Safety (before every commit)

- Verify every `require_once` path exists in the WordPress ZIP package.
- Verify no duplicate class declarations.
- Verify all modules load via `module.php` independently.
- Verify activation produces no Fatal Error on **WordPress 6.x + PHP 7.4**.
- Verify REST endpoints register on `rest_api_init` without error.

Run: `scripts/audit-activation.ps1` against `dist/package-staging/yooy-ai-studio`.
